{
  "info": {
    "name": "Companionship — Go Backend Gateway",
    "_postman_id": "backend-gw-v3-2026",
    "description": "Public Go API gateway for Companionship at http://localhost:3001.\n\nGateway strips the leading `/api` prefix when forwarding to internal services:\n  /api/auth/*           → auth   (HTTP_PORT_AUTH, default 8083)\n  /api/profile, /api/profile/* → auth\n  /api/conversations[/...]    → chat   (HTTP_PORT_CHAT, default 8081)\n  /api/voice/options          → chat\n  /api/voice/synthesize       → chat\n  /api/memories[/...]         → memory (HTTP_PORT_MEMORY, default 8082)\n  /agentic/*                  → agentic FastAPI (only when PUBLIC_AGENTIC_PROXY_ENABLED=1)\n\nAuth automation:\n  • Register/Login captures `user_id`, `token`, and `csrf_token` (parsed from the axis_csrf Set-Cookie header) into collection variables.\n  • Collection-level pre-request script auto-injects `Authorization: Bearer {{token}}` and `X-CSRF-Token: {{csrf_token}}` on every request. This means the Bearer path bypasses CSRF when token is present, and the cookie path still validates correctly if you intentionally remove Authorization.\n  • Start session captures `conversation_id`. Send message captures `message_id`. Create memory captures `memory_id`.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "gateway_url",     "value": "http://localhost:3001", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "user_id",         "value": "",                      "type": "string" },
    { "key": "token",           "value": "",                      "type": "string" },
    { "key": "csrf_token",      "value": "",                      "type": "string" },
    { "key": "conversation_id", "value": "",                      "type": "string" },
    { "key": "message_id",      "value": "",                      "type": "string" },
    { "key": "memory_id",       "value": "",                      "type": "string" }
  ],
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Auto-inject Authorization + X-CSRF-Token on every request that doesn't already set them.",
          "// Bearer bypasses CSRF in the server middleware; X-CSRF-Token is the fallback for cookie-only flows.",
          "const token = pm.collectionVariables.get('token');",
          "const csrf  = pm.collectionVariables.get('csrf_token');",
          "const hasAuth = pm.request.headers.has('Authorization');",
          "const hasCsrf = pm.request.headers.has('X-CSRF-Token');",
          "if (!hasAuth && token) {",
          "  pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'Authorization', value: 'Bearer ' + token });",
          "}",
          "if (!hasCsrf && csrf) {",
          "  pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'X-CSRF-Token', value: csrf });",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Gateway liveness",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{gateway_url}}/health",
            "description": "Unauthenticated gateway liveness probe."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth & Profile",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const r = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (r.data && r.data.user) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('user_id', r.data.user.id);",
                  "  if (r.data.token) pm.collectionVariables.set('token', r.data.token);",
                  "  // Parse axis_csrf from Set-Cookie headers (server emits it as non-HttpOnly).",
                  "  const setCookies = pm.response.headers.all().filter(h => h.key.toLowerCase() === 'set-cookie');",
                  "  for (const h of setCookies) {",
                  "    const m = String(h.value).match(/(?:^|;\\s*)axis_csrf=([^;]+)/);",
                  "    if (m) { pm.collectionVariables.set('csrf_token', m[1]); break; }",
                  "  }",
                  "  console.log('Registered:', r.data.user.id, 'token?', !!r.data.token, 'csrf?', !!pm.collectionVariables.get('csrf_token'));",
                  "} else {",
                  "  console.warn('Register: no user in response — token/csrf NOT captured');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{gateway_url}}/api/auth/register",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"test@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"testpassword123\",\n  \"displayName\": \"Test User\",\n  \"preferredLanguage\": \"id\",\n  \"safetyTermsAccepted\": true,\n  \"safetyTermsVersion\": \"2025-01\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Register a new user. Auto-captures user_id and token. The server also sets HttpOnly session + axis_csrf cookies for browser flows."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const r = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (r.data && r.data.user) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('user_id', r.data.user.id);",
                  "  if (r.data.token) pm.collectionVariables.set('token', r.data.token);",
                  "  const setCookies = pm.response.headers.all().filter(h => h.key.toLowerCase() === 'set-cookie');",
                  "  for (const h of setCookies) {",
                  "    const m = String(h.value).match(/(?:^|;\\s*)axis_csrf=([^;]+)/);",
                  "    if (m) { pm.collectionVariables.set('csrf_token', m[1]); break; }",
                  "  }",
                  "  console.log('Logged in:', r.data.user.id, 'token?', !!r.data.token, 'csrf?', !!pm.collectionVariables.get('csrf_token'));",
                  "} else {",
                  "  console.warn('Login: no user in response — token/csrf NOT captured');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{gateway_url}}/api/auth/login",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"test@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"testpassword123\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Login and auto-capture user_id + token."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Current session",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{gateway_url}}/api/auth/session",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" }],
            "description": "Returns the user behind the active session/token."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get profile",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{gateway_url}}/api/profile?userId={{user_id}}",
              "host": ["{{gateway_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "profile"],
              "query": [{ "key": "userId", "value": "{{user_id}}" }]
            },
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" }]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update profile",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "url": "{{gateway_url}}/api/profile",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"userId\": \"{{user_id}}\",\n  \"displayName\": \"Updated Name\",\n  \"preferredLanguage\": \"id\",\n  \"preferredVoiceId\": \"\",\n  \"preferredTtsModel\": \"v2_5_turbo\"\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Personality insights",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{gateway_url}}/api/profile/personality-insights",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" }],
            "description": "Returns Big Five personality scores (stub baseline until enough conversation history is available)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Generate insights",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{gateway_url}}/api/profile/generate-insights",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" }],
            "description": "Trigger a (re)compute of personality insights. Same handler as GET in this build."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
